<meta property="og:title" content="Attention-Deficit/Hyperactivity Disorder, Teen" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Attention-deficit/hyperactivity disorder is a neurobehavioral disorder characterized by a combination of inattention, hyperactivity, and impulsive behavior. In teenagers, symptoms related to inattention can include problems maintaining attention on school or homework, frequently losing important possessions, and struggling to organize or complete multi-step tasks. Hyperactivity symptoms can include being fidgety, restless, and talking or interrupting others excessively; teens may also struggle to manage impulsive or reckless behavior." />
